gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 105, Thunder 98
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Thunder, 105-98. Kevin Huerter led the way with 28 points, nine rebounds, and three steals for the Kings, while Domantas Sabonis added a triple double (17 points, 13 rebounds, and 13 assists) in the victory. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander tallied 33 points, seven rebounds, and six assists for the Thunder in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 1-0 in West Group C play, and 4-4 in the regular season, while the Thunder fall to 0-2 in West Group C play, and 5-4 in the regular season.
